ultrafast x ray summer school 2010 uxss 2010 slac national accelerator laboratory uxss 2010 uxss 2010 home registration payment information speakers program social events travel & directions accommodations location visa information contact us pulse and uxss uxss home past uxss events pulse postdoc fellowship ultrafast x ray summer school 2010 june 21 24 2010 kavli auditorium slac national accelerator laboratory menlo park ca the ultrafast x ray summer school is a four day residential program hosted annually by stanford university's pulse institute the goal is to disseminate information and train students and post docs on new opportunities in ultrafast science particularly using x ray free electron lasers lectures will be presented by expert scientists in this exciting new field the attendees will be expected to participate in the discussions and will prepare a mock beamtime proposal poster with input from the instrument scientists for the linac coherent light source important dates may 21 2010 early registration deadline june 21 2010 welcome reception june 22 2010 optional local nature hike june 23 2010 bbq social june 24 2010 poster session registration registration is now open the fee is $250 after may 21 2010 the fee will be $300 register now announcements rooms are available at the stanford guest house located on slac's campus please mention uxss 2010 when you make your reservation please reserve early to ensure availability make reservations register now reserve accommodations poster download the uxss 2010 poster your browser does not have the ability to display inline frames you can view the content of this frame at this page slac footer
